---
title: Teriyaki Pork Chop Rice Bowls  fried egg, stir-fried broccoli, corn & edamame, Sriracha
description: This rice bowl is the perfect meal when you want something satisfying and full of flavor. Fragrant and fluffy jasmine rice is the foundation for a colorful stir-fry of broccoli, corn, and edamame. Add sliced pork that’s coated in a sweet and spicy teriyaki Sriracha sauce, plus a quick fried egg, for a seriously beautiful bowl.

***Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.***

***Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.***
